It‚Äôs a tough job, but for those of us who are called to do it - it‚Äôs our life‚Äôs mission. So please take time to show your gratitude to a police officer in whatever way you can, not just this week, but everyday of the year.

As an LEO, I understand firsthand what it is like to not know if you are truly making a difference. A simple thank you goes a long way. As well as a donation to a police organization. And yes, even dropping off sweet treats to your local police station is very much appreciated.

This Police Week, I implore you to take a moment to put yourselves in their shoes. Think about the courage it takes to put on a uniform and patrol the streets each day. What it takes to keep us all safe. https://t.co/NYYSF4emdI
